HEADWORD: Colostrum
<hw>Co*los"trum</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.,
biestings.]</ety> <fld>(Med.)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>The first milk
secreted after delivery; biestings.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>A mixture of
turpentine and the yolk of an egg, formerly used as an
emulsion.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

